item.title: I want run server with eclipse but have some problem
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Looks like your server is trying to run with Java 1.6

In the Package Explorer, right click your project and click properties (at the bottom)

Click on the “Java Compiler” text in the tree (Has a carrot > next to it)
Now, one would hope that all the setting are all grayed out (meaning you cannot edit them) except for the “Enable project specific settings” box.
(If not it really doesn’t matter)

Your compiler compliance level, Generated .class files compatibility, and Source compatibility should be set to 1.8.

If they are not, click on the blue “Configure Workspace Settings…” and change the compliance to 1.8.
^That’s for if it’s grayed out.
If the settings are NOT grayed out, then do not click that, and just change it to 1.8 on the compliance level (The other boxes should change with it)
